genresAdvancedInfo.name: italian baritone
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Italian baritone music is characterized by a deep, rich, and powerful vocal range. This genre is often associated with classical opera, but it can also be found in other genres such as pop and jazz. Famous Italian baritone singers include Luciano Pavarotti, Andrea Bocelli, and Franco Corelli.
